# === JSON_PARTIAL_OUTPUT_ON_ERROR (now honored) ===
# 003, 004, inf_nan_error, unsupported_type_error: all unskipped after
# implementing the flag at the encoder's value-level error sites.
# json_encode_recursion_01/02 stay skiplisted: those need the separate
# "jsonSerialize returns $this" special case (where ext/json detects
# the retval IS the original zval and falls through to property
# serialization rather than re-entering jsonSerialize).
json_encode_recursion_01.phpt # ext-json-internals # jsonSerialize returning $this
json_encode_recursion_02.phpt # ext-json-internals # jsonSerialize returning $this

# === JSON_INVALID_UTF8_IGNORE / SUBSTITUTE (honored) ===
# fastjson honors both flags with ext/json-matching semantics:
# IGNORE strips invalid bytes, SUBSTITUTE replaces with U+FFFD.
# Encode follows php_next_utf8_char's maximal-subpart advance;
# decode does per-byte advance on invalid (mirroring ext/json's
# parser). The walker splits on the flag at decode entry so the
# no-flag hot path is unchanged.

# === History: previously-skipped items now passing ===
# Decode $depth validation: resolved by argument validation + the
# decode depth-walker landing in v0.1.0.
# Uppercase \uXXXX hex: resolved by vendor patch P-001 (see
# vendor/yyjson/PATCHES.md). ~8 of the previously-skipped tests now
# pass cleanly. The entries below failed for *other* reasons that
# happened to coincide with the hex divergence and are re-listed
# under their primary cause.

# === UTF-8 handling ===
# After fastjson honors JSON_INVALID_UTF8_IGNORE / SUBSTITUTE,
# several of the old UTF-8 + PARTIAL_OUTPUT tests pass cleanly
# (bug43941, bug55543, bug61978, bug63737, bug68567, bug72787,
# bug73991). The entries below still fail for orthogonal reasons:
#  - ext/json's specific "Malformed UTF-8 characters" wording,
#  - JSON_ERROR_CTRL_CHAR (code 3) which yyjson doesn't surface,
#  - NUL-byte filtering in stdClass property names,
#  - and one pending memory-leak in encode + jsonSerialize +
#    PARTIAL_OUTPUT (bug77843, fastjson-side bug to investigate).
bug54484.phpt # ext-json-internals # error code numbering for UTF-8 within JSON
bug61537.phpt # ext-json-internals # ext/json UTF-8 message text
bug62010.phpt # ext-json-internals # ext/json UTF-8 message text
bug68546.phpt # ext-json-internals # NUL bytes in property names
bug69187.phpt # ext-json-internals # JSON_ERROR_CTRL_CHAR code numbering
bug77843.phpt # bug-report # memory leak in encode + JsonSerializable + PARTIAL_OUTPUT

# === Object property keys with embedded NUL (ext/json strips them) ===
bug66021.phpt # ext-json-internals # NUL bytes in property names

# === U+2028 / U+2029 line separator escaping ===
# ext/json always escapes U+2028 and U+2029 (even with UNESCAPED_UNICODE)
# because JSONP / older JS engines break on bare line separators inside
# string literals. yyjson treats them as ordinary code points unless
# YYJSON_WRITE_ESCAPE_UNICODE forces \uXXXX for the whole string.
json_encode_u2028_u2029.phpt # doc-divergence # U+2028/U+2029 not specially escaped

